<paragraph blockId="53.[144,1101,855,1166]" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382">
<taxonomicName authority="Meregalli &amp; Borovec, 2011" authorityName="Meregalli &amp; Borovec" authorityYear="2011" box="[144,290,855,879]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friedmani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[144,290,855,879]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382">Ita friedmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[300,387,855,879]" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, from the Negev desert, is the closest geographically; it differs in its larger size, the rostrum broader at its base and scarcely widened apicad, and the denser elytral vestiture, with scales forming weakly raised rows along the striae; the aedeagus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Meregalli &amp; Borovec, 2011" authorityName="Meregalli &amp; Borovec" authorityYear="2011" box="[285,415,951,975]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="friedmani" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[285,415,951,975]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382">I. friedmani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[423,508,951,974]" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is different, it being long and slender, with narrowly sclerotized sides. 
<taxonomicName authority="Meregalli &amp; Borovec, 2011" authorityName="Meregalli &amp; Borovec" authorityYear="2011" box="[337,476,982,1006]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="korotyaevi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[337,476,982,1006]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382">I. korotyaevi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[483,568,983,1006]" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
also has an aedeagus with narrowly sclerotized sides, but its elytral vestiture is denser, composed of shorter scales and its rostrum is more slender. The western Mediterranean species usually have shorter scales, with much denser vestiture and, except 
<taxonomicName box="[525,642,1078,1102]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chobauti">
<emphasis box="[525,642,1078,1102]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382">I. chobauti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an aedeagus with more or less expanded membranous part in the centre; also 
<taxonomicName authority="Meregalli &amp; Borovec, 2011" authorityName="Meregalli &amp; Borovec" authorityYear="2011" box="[565,693,1110,1134]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hispanica" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[565,693,1110,1134]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382">I. hispanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[699,787,1111,1134]" pageId="53" pageNumber="1382" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, which has similarly slender scales, has an aedeagus with narrowly sclerotized margins.
</paragraph>
